com.camerontec.catalys.core.marketstate

Interface IMarketMirror

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IService
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FixMarketMirror, FixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive, SynchronizedFixMarketMirror, SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive

    public interface IMarketMirror
extends IService, IConfigurable
    A "market mirror" processes messages to and from a market and uses them to construct the state of the market, consisting of orders and associated fills.

    The current state of all orders and fills in the market can be queried by tag/value.

    See Also:
    IRequestHistoryEntry

      • getOrder

        ITagValues getOrder(String clOrdID)
        Retrieves the order associated with the given ClOrdID.

        This is equivalent to the tag/value getOrder call where the tag indicates ClOrdID.

        Note that you can use any ClOrdID associated with the order. An order that has been amended will have more than one associated ClOrdID.

        Parameters:
        clOrdID - A ClOrdID associated with an order.
        Returns:
        null if no such order.
